Preheat broiler. Mix meat, 2 Tbsp. of the barbecue sauce, crumbs and egg. Shape into 4 patties. Place on rack of broiler pan. Broil 4 to 6 inches from heat 7 to 9 minutes on each side or until cooked through (160 degrees F), brushing frequently with the remaining barbecue sauce. Top with Singles; broil until Singles begin to melt. Fill buns with patties. Top with additional burger toppings, if desired.